  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00005_196916_1517807321216&sectionId=34298&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00005_196916_1517807321216
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act "President", "Vice-President" and "Second Schedule" shall mean the`
  line `President of India, the Vice-President of India and the Second Schedule to the Constitution respectively.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (34299)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Discharge of President’s functions in certain contingencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00005_196916_1517807321216&sectionId=34299&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00005_196916_1517807321216
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the event of the occurrence`
  line `of vacancies in the offices of both the President and the Vice-President, by reason in each case of death,`
  line `resignation or removal, or otherwise, the Chief Justice of India or, in his absence, the seniormost Judge of`
  line `the Supreme Court of India available shall discharge the functions of the President until a new President`
  line `elected in accordance with the provisions of the Constitution to fill the vacancy in the office of the`
  line `President enters upon his office or a new Vice-President so elected begins to act as President under`
  line `article 65 of the Constitution, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Vice-President, while discharging the functions of the President, dies, resigns, or is`
  line `removed or otherwise ceases to hold office, the Chief Justice of India or, in his absence, the seniormost`
  line `Judge referred to in sub-section (1) shall discharge the said functions until the President resumes his`
  line `duties or a new Vice-President is elected as aforesaid, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(3) When the Vice-President,—`
  line
  line `(a) while acting as President, or`
  line
  line `(b) while discharging the functions of the President,`
  line
  line `is unable to discharge the functions of the President owing to absence, illness or any other cause, the`
  line `Chief Justice of India or, in his absence, the seniormost Judge referred to in sub-section (1) shall`
  line `discharge the said functions—`
  line
  line `(i) in the case referred to in clause (a), until a new President elected as aforesaid enters upon`
  line `his office or until the Vice-President acting as President resumes his duties, whichever is earlier;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case referred to in clause (b), until the President resumes his duties, or the`
  line `Vice-President resumes his duties, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(4) The person discharging the functions of the President under this section shall, during, and in`
  line `respect of, the period while he is so discharging the said functions, have all the powers and immunities of`
  line `the President and be entitled to such emoluments, allowances and privileges as may be determined by`
  line `Parliament by law and, until provision in that behalf is so made, such emoluments, allowances and`
  line `privileges as are specified in the Second Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
